The paper examines factors associated with citation and altmetric counts for academic papers, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on journal impact factor, collaboration, institution prestige, and research funding suggests that it could be related to digital libraries (cs.DL) or information retrieval (cs.IR). The analysis of abstract and title length and readability could also be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) or human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The investigation of altmetric events such as Twitter and Facebook posts could be related to social computing (cs.SI) or cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). Finally, the consideration of field size and type could be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) or systems and control (cs.SY).
